Marcus Rashford, Jamie Vardy and Danny Ings were the only players in the top 10 to score over the weekend. Rashford netted in Manchester United’s 1-1 draw with Liverpool on Sunday, while Vardy claimed one goal in Leicester City’s 2-1 win over Burnley. Ings was on target at Southampton took a point from their trip to Wolves. Sergio Aguero, Tammy Abraham, Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang and Raheem Sterling all failed to score on Match Day 9. Premier League top scorers: 8 goals: Sergio Aguero (Manchester City), Tammy Abraham (Chelsea) 7 goals: Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang (Arsenal) 6 goals: Teemu Pukki (Norwich), Raheem Sterling (Manchester City), Jamie Vardy (Leicester) 5 goals: Harry Kane (Tottenham), Callum Wilson (Bournemouth), Sadio Mane (Liverpool) 4 goals: Mohamed Salah (Liverpool), Ashley Barnes (Burnley), Bernardo Silva (Manchester City), Danny Ings (Southampton), Marcus Rashford (Manchester United), Sebastien Haller (West Ham), Wesley (Aston Villa), Chris Wood (Burnley), Mason Mount (Chelsea) Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.